{"lemma":"حَلَّ","slug":"حَلَّ","root":"ح.ل.ل","root_slug":"ح-ل-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-ل-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"حَلَّ","root":"حلل","pos":"N","occurrence_count":5},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":5,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":22},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n8734"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%8E%D9%84%D9%8E%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to unfasten; to untie; to unknot; to unravel; to disentangle; to loosen","tags":["transitive"],"examples":[{"text":"وَاحْلُلْ عُقْدَةً مِّن لِّسَانِي"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to unfasten; to untie; to unknot; to unravel; to disentangle; to loosen; to solve, to find an answer to or a solution for (something, such as a problem); to untangle; to crack","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to liquefy; to dissolve","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to liquefy; to dissolve; to turn into a solution","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to invalidate, to deprive of effective legal or otherwise binding power; to dissolve","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to invalidate, to deprive of effective legal or otherwise binding power; to dissolve; to breach (a contract, an agreement, an oath, and the like); to break","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to settle; to approach","examples":[{"text":"فَلَأَنْتَ أَنْتَ إِذَاْ حَلَلْتَ بــ: طَيْبَةٍ","english":"For when you, approach goodness(طيبة) (one of the names of Madinah)"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to dismount; to stop, to halt","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to stay, to settle","tags":["intransitive","transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to visit","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to live in, to reside in (a place)","tags":["transitive"],"examples":[{"text":"وَلَا يَزَالُ الَّذِينَ كَفَرُوا تُصِيبُهُم بِمَا صَنَعُوا قَارِعَةٌ أَوْ تَحُلُّ قَرِيبًا مِّن دَارِهِمْ حَتَّىٰ يَأْتِيَ وَعْدُ اللَّهِ","english":"If there were a recitation that could cause mountains to move, or the earth to split, or the dead to speak, «it would have been this Quran». But all matters are by Allah’s Will. Have the believers not yet realized that had Allah willed, He could have guided all of humanity? And disasters will continue to afflict the disbelievers or strike close to their homes for their misdeeds, until Allah’s promise comes to pass. Surely Allah never fails in His promise."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to occupy, to take (someone's place)","tags":["transitive"],"examples":[{"text":"كان في أحد الأكياس تشكيلة من البسكويت القديم الذي اندثر من بقالات صنعاء وغيرها من المدن. هذه الأنواع من البسكويت كانت متوفرة عندما كنت صغيراً وعمري على ما أذكر 4–7 سنوات، ثمّ اختفت بالتدريج، وحلّت محلّها أصناف أخرى.","english":"In one of the bags there was a pack of ancient biscuits the kind of which disappeared from most grocers of Ṣanʻāʼ and other cities. This type of biscuit was widespread when I small and my age, as I remember, 4–7, then it left sight gradually, and other kinds took its place."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to descend, to go down"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to occur, to happen"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to befall [with بِ (bi) or عَلَى (ʕalā) ‘someone’] (of punishment, suffering, hatred or something else negative)","examples":[{"text":"كُلُوا مِنْ طَيِّبَاتِ مَا رَزَقْنَاكُمْ وَلَا تَطْغَوْا فِيهِ فَيَحِلَّ عَلَيْكُمْ غَضَبِي وَمَنْ يَحْلِلْ عَلَيْهِ غَضَبِي فَقَدْ هَوَىٰ","english":"Eat of the good things wherewith We have provided you, and transgress not in respect thereof lest My wrath come upon you: and he on whom My wrath cometh, he is lost indeed."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to overwhelm [with عَلَى (ʕalā) ‘someone’] (of sleep)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to arrive, to begin (of a season or time)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to become incarnate [with فِي (fī) ‘in someone’] (of God)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be or become permissible or lawful","tags":["intransitive"],"examples":[{"text":"وَلَا يَحِلُّ لَكُمْ أَنْ تَأْخُذُوا مِمَّا آتَيْتُمُوهُنَّ شَيْئًا","english":"And it is not permissible for you that ye take aught of what ye have given them."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of حَلَّ (ḥalla) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a solution","tags":["countable"],"examples":[{"text":"لِكُلِّ مُشْكِلَةٍ أَلْفُ حَلٍّ.","english":"For every problem, there are a thousand solutions."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"sesame, or sesame oil","tags":["obsolete"],"examples":[{"text":"وتعجن بدهن اللوز أو الحل، الشربة منه حبة إلى دانقين بسمن بقر أو بدهن الحل.","english":"And knead with almond oil or sesame oil, the dose of it is one pill to two dāniq, with butter or with sesame oil."},{"text":"دهن الحلّ هو عند الرازي غير دهن السمسم وهو عند الإسرائيلي وفي كتاب مسيح دهن الحلّ أي الشيرج الذي لم يقشر سمسمه.","english":"Duhn al-ḥall is according to Rhazes not sesame oil but according to al-Isrāʾīlīy and Masīh duhn al-ḥall or šīraj is that where the sesame has not been peeled."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root ح ل ل (ḥ l l). Compare Hebrew חל.\nThe meaning of “sesame oil” may derive via a chain of calques from Akkadian 𒉌𒄑 (ellum), which is also homographic to 𒉌𒄑 (šamnum, “oil”), that, to build a bridge, might suggest that Aramaic חָלָא / ܚܠܐ (ḥallā) also had this meaning but has consistently been misread as more common “vinegar”, the etymon of Arabic خَلّ (ḵall, “vinegar”), if not other homographs, due to complete merger of ḥ and ḫ more likely than in Arabic itself where it also happens due to taṣḥīf."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n8734","headword_ar":"حَلَّ","root":"Hl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hal~N","text_ar":"حَلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He untied,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"undid,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"opened,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,) a knot: (S, Mgh, Msb, K:) this is the primary signification. (Er-Rághib, TA.) Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaA EaAqidu A@*okuro Hal~FA","text_ar":"يَا عَاقِدُ ا@ذْكُرْ حَلًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O tyer of a knot, bear in mind"},{"kind":"text","text":"the time of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"untying:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAbilu","text_ar":"حَابِلُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O binder,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tyer, of the rope:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hbl","text_ar":"حبل"},{"kind":"text","text":":)] (S, TA:) or, as IAar relates it,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yA HaAmilu","text_ar":"يا حَامِلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O loader"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: a prov., applied to the consideration of results; because a man may tie a load too tightly; and when he desires to untie it, may injure himself and his camel. (TA. [See also a similar saying below, in the second paragraph.]) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~ufoEapu kaHal~i","text_ar":"الشُّفْعَةُ كَحَلِّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEiqaAli","text_ar":"العِقَالِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The right of preemption is like the untying of the cord with which a camel's fore shank and arm are bound together"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: meaning that it is accomplished as quickly and easily as the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EqAl","text_ar":"عقال"},{"kind":"text","text":"is untied: the explanation that it passes away quickly, like the camel when his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EqAl","text_ar":"عقال"},{"kind":"text","text":"is untied, is improbable. (Mgh, Msb. *) And hence the saying [in the Kur xx. 28],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wa A@Holulo EuqodapF mino lisaAniY","text_ar":"وَ ا@حْلُلْ عُقْدَةً مِنْ لِسَانِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And loose Thou an impediment of,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from, my tongue"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Er-Rághib, TA.) The pass. is pronounced by some"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hul~a","text_ar":"حُلَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and by others"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hil~a","text_ar":"حِلَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": thus in the saying of El-Farezdak,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"famaA Hil~a mino jaholK HubaY HulamaAy^inaA\n                      \n                     \n                        wa laA qaAbilu AlmaEoruwfi fiynaA yuEan~afu"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And the garments of our forbearing men by which they support themselves in sitting by binding them,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"making them tight, round the shanks and back are not loosed through ignorance, nor is the accepter of the benefit, among us, reproached"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; the kesreh of the first"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"l","text_ar":"ل"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the original form"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hulila","text_ar":"حُلِلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] being transferred to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"H","text_ar":"ح"},{"kind":"text","text":": but Akh heard it pronounced in this instance"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hul~a","text_ar":"حُلَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and some, he says, in this word, and in others like it, as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rud~a","text_ar":"رُدَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ud~a","text_ar":"شُدَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", only impart to the dammeh somewhat of the sound of kesreh, by the pronunciation termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_i$omaAm","text_ar":"اـِشْمَام"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) ―         -b2-  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, dissolved, melted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"liquefied,"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hl~l","text_ar":"حلّل","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taHoliylN","text_ar":"تَحْلِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", often said of a medicine as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it acted as a dissolvent."},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hul~a","text_ar":"حُلَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) inf. n. as above, (TA,) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It was dissolved, melted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"liquefied,"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said of anything congealed, frozen, or solid. (M, K.) ―         -b3-  [(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He solved"},{"kind":"text","text":"a problem, or riddle, &c. ―         -b4-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He analyzed"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hl~l","text_ar":"حلّل","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n. as above.] ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hal~a Alyamiyna","text_ar":"حَلَّ اليَمِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 2. ―         -b6-  From"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hal~u AlA^aHomaAli Einoda","text_ar":"حَلُّ الاَحْمَالِ عِنْدَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~uzuwli","text_ar":"النُّزُولِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The untying, unbinding,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"loosing, of the loads on the occasion of alighting"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hal~a","text_ar":"حَلَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuluwlN","text_ar":"حُلُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", came to be used alone as meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nazala","text_ar":"نَزَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He alighted;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"descended and stopped"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sojourned"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abode"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lodged"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"settled;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and simply"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he took up his abode;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he abode, lodged,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"settled;"},{"kind":"text","text":"in a place]. (Er-Rághib, TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hal~a biAlomakaAni","text_ar":"حَلَّ بِالْمَكَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAlobaladi","text_ar":"بِالْبَلَدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hal~a AlmakaAna","text_ar":"حَلَّ المَكَانَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, * K) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Albalada","text_ar":"البَلَدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) both of which forms of the aor. are mentioned by Ibn-Málik, (TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuluwlN","text_ar":"حُلُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hal~N","text_ar":"حَلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HalalN","text_ar":"حَلَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is extr., (K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHal~N","text_ar":"مَحَلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHil~N","text_ar":"مَحِلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bihi","text_ar":"بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHtl~","text_ar":"احتلّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHtl~hu","text_ar":"احتلّهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nazala bihi","text_ar":"نَزَلَ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He alighted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"descended and stopped"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. (as above),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the place"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the country"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"town"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (Msb, K, TA.) And in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hal~a biAlqawomi","text_ar":"حَلَّ بِالقَوْمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hal~a Alqawoma","text_ar":"حَلَّ القَوْمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, ISd, TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bihimo","text_ar":"بِهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHtl~","text_ar":"احتلّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHtl~humo","text_ar":"احتلّهُمْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISd, TA) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He alighted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"descended and stopped &c., at,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in, the abode of the people"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"party"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hal~a A_ilaY","text_ar":"حَلَّ اـِلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alqawom","text_ar":"القَوْم"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hul~a AlmakaAnu","text_ar":"حُلَّ المَكَانُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The place was alighted in,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"taken as an abode;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was inhabited."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) [Hence, in philosophy,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuluwlN","text_ar":"حُلُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Temporary"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"separable,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"permanent"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inseparable, indwelling"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inbeing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hal~a bihi","text_ar":"حَلَّ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiyhi","text_ar":"فِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It had,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became in the condition of having, such indwelling"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inbeing in it."},{"kind":"text","text":"And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hal~a bihi","text_ar":"حَلَّ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiyhi","text_ar":"فِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is often said of joy and grief and the like, meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It took up its abode in him."},{"kind":"text","text":"And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ka*aA","text_ar":"كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hal~a maHal~a","text_ar":"حَلَّ مَحَلَّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It took,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"occupied, the place of such a thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b7-  And hence, (TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hal~a AlhadoYu","text_ar":"حَلَّ الهَدْىُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hil~apN","text_ar":"حِلَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuluwlN","text_ar":"حُلُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The beasts for sacrifice arrived at the place where it was lawful for them to be sacrificed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at the place in which they should be sacrificed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hal~a","text_ar":"حَلَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of a punishment has for its aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":", and the inf. n. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuluwlN","text_ar":"حُلُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) [but it is said that]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hal~a AlEa*aAbu","text_ar":"حَلَّ العَذَابُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The punishment alighted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"descended:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hal~a","text_ar":"حَلَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, due,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"necessitated by the requirements of justice to take effect:"},{"kind":"text","text":"it is said in the Kur [xx. 83],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fayaHul~a Ealayokumo gaDabiY","text_ar":"فَيَحُلَّ عَلَيْكُمْ غَضَبِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"test my anger alight upon you,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"befall you"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fayaHil~a","text_ar":"فَيَحِلَّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Elykm","text_ar":"عليكم"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"test it become due to you"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; accord. to different readings: (S, O:) or when you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hal~a bihimo AlEa*aAbu","text_ar":"حَلَّ بِهِمْ العَذَابُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [you mean (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The punishment alighted upon them,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"befell them;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and] the aor. is"},{"kind":"text","text":"only: and when you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hal~a EalaY~a","text_ar":"حَلَّ عَلَىَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laka","text_ar":"لَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [you mean (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It became due to me,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to thee;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and] the aor. is"},{"kind":"text","text":":"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ano yaHul~a Ealayokumo gaDabN mino rab~ikumo","text_ar":"اَنْ يَحُلَّ عَلَيْكُمْ غَضَبٌ مِنْ رَبِّكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the Kur xx. 89,] means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that anger should alight upon you,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"befall you, from your Lord"},{"kind":"text","text":"[accord. to those who read thus instead of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaHil~a","text_ar":"يَحِلَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but the latter is the common reading]. (TA.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hal~a A^amoru A@ll~`hi Ealayohi","text_ar":"حَلَّ اَمْرُ ا@للّٰهِ عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuluwlN","text_ar":"حُلُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The threatened punishment of God"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, due to him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"necessitated by the requirements of justice to take effect upon him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hal~a Haq~iY Ealayohi","text_ar":"حَلَّ حَقِّى عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, * K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuluwlN","text_ar":"حُلُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHil~N","text_ar":"مَحِلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"My right,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"due, was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, a thing the rendering of which was obligatory,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"incumbent, on him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, * K, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hal~a Ald~ayonu","text_ar":"حَلَّ الدَّيْنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuluwlN","text_ar":"حُلُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S Msb,) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The debt was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fell, due;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its appointed term,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"period, ended,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so that the payment of it became due."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hal~a Ealayohi Ald~ayonu","text_ar":"حَلَّ عَلَيْهِ الدَّيْنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The payment of the debt became obligatory on him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.) ―         -b9-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hal~a","text_ar":"حَلَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hil~N","text_ar":"حِلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HalaAlN","text_ar":"حَلَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a thing, S, Mgh, Msb)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, lawful, allowable,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"free;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA;)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laka","text_ar":"لَكَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to thee:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haruma","text_ar":"حَرُمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb, K:) a metaphorical signification, from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hal~u AlEuqodapi","text_ar":"حَلُّ العُقْدَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[“ the untying of the knot ”]. (TA.) Hence the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alz~awoju A^aHaq~u","text_ar":"الزَّوْجُ اَحَقُّ"},{"kind":"page_break","n":620},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"birajoEatihaA maA lamo taHil~a lahaA AlSalaApu","text_ar":"بِرَجْعَتِهَا مَا لَمْ تَحِلَّ لَهَا الصَلَاةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The husband is entitled to taking her back to the marriage-state as long as prayer is not lawful to her"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Mgh.) And the saying, in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lam~aA raA^aY Al$~amosa qado","text_ar":"لَمَّا رَاَى الشَّمْسَ قَدْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waqabato qaAla h`*aA Hiynu Hil~ihaA","text_ar":"وَقَبَتْ قَالَ هٰذَا حِينُ حِلِّهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"When he saw that the sun had set, he said,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is the time of its becoming lawful;"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning the prayer of sunset. (TA.) ―         -b10-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hal~a","text_ar":"حَلَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hil~N","text_ar":"حِلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, free from,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quit of, an obligation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"responsibility.]"},{"kind":"text","text":"You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaEalahu fiY Hil~K mino qibalihi","text_ar":"جَعَلَهُ فِى حِلٍّ مِنْ قِبَلِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pronounced him, free from,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quit of, obligation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"responsibility, with respect to him."},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anota fiY Hil~K mino ka*aA","text_ar":"اَنْتَ فِى حِلٍّ مِنْ كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou art free from,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quit of, obligation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"responsibility, with respect to such a thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"] And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hal~a","text_ar":"حَلَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHorim","text_ar":"مُحْرِم"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hal~a mino A_iHoraAmihi","text_ar":"حَلَّ مِنْ اـِحْرَامِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HalaAlN","text_ar":"حَلَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hil~N","text_ar":"حِلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) or both; (TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHl~","text_ar":"احلّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tHl~l","text_ar":"تحلّل","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Bd and Jel in ii. 192;) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He quitted his state of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iHoraAm","text_ar":"اـِحْرَام"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb, K:) this, also, is a metaphorical signification, from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hal~u AlEuqodapi","text_ar":"حَلُّ العُقْدَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEalahu fiY Hil~ihi wa Hiromihi","text_ar":"فَعَلَهُ فِى حِلِّهِ وَ حِرْمِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wHuromihi","text_ar":"وحُرْمِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fY Hul~ihi","text_ar":"فى حُلِّهِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He did it when he was free from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iHoraAm","text_ar":"اـِحْرَام"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and when he was in the state of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHrAm","text_ar":"احرام"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uhuwru AlHil~i","text_ar":"شُهُورُ الحِلِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$ohuru AlHil~i","text_ar":"اَشْهُرُ الحِلِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hil~N","text_ar":"حِلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below, And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hal~ati AlmaroA^apu","text_ar":"حَلَّتِ المَرْاَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) [aor."},{"kind":"text","text":",] inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hil~N","text_ar":"حِلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuluwlN","text_ar":"حُلُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The woman quitted her"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"period termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eid~ap","text_ar":"عِدَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K:) this, too, is a metaphorical signification, from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hal~u AlEuqodapi","text_ar":"حَلُّ العُقْدَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hal~ato","text_ar":"حَلَّتْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lilz~awaAji","text_ar":"لِلزَّوَاجِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"she became free from any obstacle to marriage, as, for instance, by having accomplished the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eid~ap","text_ar":"عِدَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) [And (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The woman became free from the marriage tie, by the death of her husband,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by divorce."},{"kind":"text","text":"] You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anoti fiY Hil~K min~iY","text_ar":"اَنْتِ فِى حِلٍّ مِنِّى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou art divorced from me."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hal~ati","text_ar":"حَلَّتِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alyamiynu","text_ar":"اليَمِينُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The oath"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became discharged;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and thus,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"proved true."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b11-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hal~a","text_ar":"حَلَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hal~N","text_ar":"حَلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He ran."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hal~a bihi","text_ar":"حَلَّ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 4.       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hal~a","text_ar":"حَلَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", sec. pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Halilota","text_ar":"حَلِلْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HalalN","text_ar":"حَلَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"had a pain in his hips and"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the CK “ or ”]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his knees."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HalalN","text_ar":"حَلَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below.]"}],"source_refs":["S","Mgh","Msb","K","TA","M","ISd","O"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}